for morphological description format, pholidotic nomenclature, and scale counts. Scale counts and morphometric measurements were performed by the first author under a stereomicroscope; bilateral meristic and qualitative characters were recorded from both sides and are presented as right/left. Morphometric measurements were taken with a caliper to the nearest 0.1 mm , except for limbs and tail which were measured with a piece of string and a ruler. We recorded a total of 10 morphometric measurements and 23 scale counts as follows: Measurements: snout-vent length ( SVL ), from tip of snout to anterior margin of vent; axilla-groin distance (AGD), from posterior border of arm insertion to anterior border of leg insertion; tail length (TL), from anterior margin of vent to tail tip; head length (HL), from tip of snout to posterior margin of tympanum; head width (HW), at maximum head width; head depth (HD), at the maximum head depth; eye-to-nares distance (EN), from center of naris to anterior border of orbit; snout length (SL), from tip of snout to anterior border of orbit; forelimb length (FLL), from axilla to tip of 3 rd finger; hind limb length (HLL), from groin to tip of 4 th toe. Scale counts: postrostrals (PR), in a transverse line juxtaposed to the posterodorsal margin of rostral; postnasals (PN), the scales posteriorly juxtaposed to the nasal; loreals (L), between postnasals and anterior border of orbit; scales in a transverse row between the 1 st and 2 nd supralabials suture of each side (SBSL); supralabials (SL); infralabials (IL); supraciliaries (SC), enlarged and flattened scales aligned on anterior and upper margin of eye forming a supraciliary flap; postmentals (PM), enlarged scales on chin juxtaposed along the posterior margin of mental; ventral scales along a midventral row, between throat and anterior border of cloaca (VMR-a), from anterior level of arms to anterior border of cloaca (VMR-b), and between anterior levels of forelimbs and hind limbs (VMR-c);