, the third lamella under the 4 th toe was counted from the tip of the toe toward the sole of the foot. We follow
for coding the pattern of subcaudal scales, where each enlarged midventral scale is represented by an Arabic number (1 for single scales and 2 for paired scales) and the number of small scales laterodistally in contact with these is denoted by single or double apostrophe (for one or two small scales, respectively).

